# Theme + shared Angular UI (`--tx-*` + `tx-*`)

**Policy:** Always use shared `tx-*` components, directives, and pipes in feature work; extend `src/app/shared/` when missing. See **`use-shared-ui.mdc`** (always applied).

Testrix separates **Electron chrome** (`electron/**`) from the **Angular shell** (`src/**`). Renderer styling is token-first (`--tx-*`) and consolidated into reusable `tx-*` atoms under `src/app/shared/`.



## Token layering



1. **Foundation** — `src/styles/_tokens.scss` defines `--tx-*` palette + structural colors (surface, text, borders, focus ring, statuses).

2. **Themes** — `src/styles/_themes.scss` swaps palettes for `body.theme-light` plus `prefers-color-scheme` overrides for `body.theme-system`. `ConfigService`-driven switches add `theme-light|dark|system` classes on `<body>`.

3. **Components** — co-located `*.component.scss` files map layout concerns to semantic tokens.



### Rules for feature authors



- No one-off `#rrggbb` in `src/app/features/**` unless you are authoring a core token bump in `_tokens.scss`.

- Compose with `color-mix(in srgb, var(--tx-*) …)` when you need tints—not arbitrary RGBA blobs.

- Use host-level `:host { display … }` and keep specificity low; escalate with BEM-ish child selectors only inside the owning component stylesheet.



## Approved shared widgets (`src/app/shared`)



| Selector | Responsibility |

| --- | --- |

| `tx-button` | Primary interaction surface (`variant`: `cta` \| `primary` \| `secondary` \| `add`). |

| `tx-modal` | Dialog chrome (backdrop card, ESC, optional backdrop dismissal). |

| `tx-form-field` | Opinionated `<label>` + projected control stacking for prototyping. |

| `tx-brand-logo` | `<img>` wrapper over `/brand/logo.svg` mirrors synced SVG from `npm run sync:brand`. |

| `tx-window-titlebar` | Frameless-shell chrome (`minimize` / maximize toggle / close) via `window.testrix.windowControls`; macOS inset padding for traffic lights. |

| `tx-error-banner` | Displays `ErrorNotificationService` payloads after Angular renders; cannot replace Electron `error.html`. |
| `tx-banner` | Presentational inline banner (`info` \| `success` \| `warning` \| `error`); optional dismiss and `[bannerActions]` slot. |
| `tx-input` | Text input with token focus ring; ControlValueAccessor. |
| `tx-variable-input` | Text input with `$` dynamic-variable autocomplete (`@shared/dynamic-variables`); ControlValueAccessor. |
| `tx-key-value-list` | Editable key/value rows (optional enable checkbox, add/remove); `valueInput="variables"` uses `tx-variable-input` on the value column. |
| `tx-textarea` | Multi-line field; optional monospace. |
| `tx-toggle` | Switch control; ControlValueAccessor. |
| `tx-slider` | Range input with filled track. |
| `tx-tag` | Status pill (`default` \| `success` \| `warning` \| `error` \| `info`). |
| `tx-spinner` | Indeterminate loader. |
| `tx-divider` | Horizontal rule. |
| `tx-tree` | Hierarchical list with expand/collapse, selection, and pointer DnD (`TxTreeConfig` drag/drop/sort policies). |
| `tx-tab` | Editor tab chip (label, optional HTTP method badge, pin, close). |
| `tx-tab-bar` | Horizontal scrollable tab strip; drag reorder and cross-pane drop. |
| `tx-split-pane` | Recursive horizontal/vertical split layout with draggable dividers. |
| `tx-settings-popup` | Settings modal (appearance, UI, collections, HTTP, logging, data, privacy, about). |
| `tx-theme-layout-preview` | Miniature theme chrome from `ThemePalette` (settings / DS). |
| `[txAutofocus]` | Simple focus helper |
| `truncate` pipe (`shared/pipes`) | Display-only truncation for previews |



## Cross-runtime contracts



- Renderer code **never imports** filesystem APIs.

- Angular talks to preload exclusively through `window.testrix` typings (`src/types/testrix-window.d.ts`). 

- Canonical settings/session shapes live under `shared/config` (+ Zod schemas) and ship to both Electron and Angular compilations.



## Anti-patterns



- Embedding raw SVG/wordmarks directly in Angular features—reuse `tx-brand-logo`.

- Introducing Tailwind/`@apply` ergonomics—the repo standard is plain SCSS + tokens.

- Duplicating enums between `shared/**` (runtime contracts) vs `src/app/shared/**` (UI kit). 



## Splash / Electron surfaces



Splash + installer-facing HTML/CSS under `electron/splash/**` deliberately diverges token sources (static bundles). Whenever you brighten/darken the renderer palette, update the Electron CSS mirrors for visual parity—or document deltas in README.

